Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease cookie sheets. In a medium bowl, beat together the shortening, egg and peppermint extract until smooth and creamy. Stir in the cake mix. Roll teaspoonfuls of dough into balls and place them 1 inch apart onto prepared cookie sheets. Bake for 8 -10 minutes in the preheated oven. Watch very closely. when they start to crack they are done.